  "text": "Cousson et al [CITATION_1] confirmed the advantages of continuous infusion (loading dose of 20 mg/kg followed by 60 mg/kg/day) over intermittent infusion (20 mg/kg over 30 minutes every 8 hours) in terms of pharmacodynamics and predictable efficacy in adult patients with VAP due to Gram-negative bacilli. The %T>MIC of ceftazidime (MIC=20 mg/L) was 100% and 46%, respectively, following continuous infusion and intermittent infusion (P<0.003).",
